  "prompt": "What countries can I travel to without an Indian passport?",
  "response": "It seems like you're asking about countries you can travel to without using your Indian passport, which implies you might have another passport or travel document. However, without specifying the other passport or travel document you possess, it's difficult to provide an accurate answer.\n\nTo clarify, if you have dual citizenship or another passport, please specify which one, and I can provide information on visa-free travel or visa-on-arrival options for that specific passport. For example:\n\n- **If you have a US passport**: You can travel to over 180 countries without a visa or with a visa on arrival, including popular destinations like the UK, Japan, and most of Europe.\n- **If you have an EU passport**: You can travel freely within the Schengen Area and to many other countries like Canada and Brazil without a visa.\n- **If you have an Australian passport**: You can visit over 180 countries visa-free or with a visa on arrival, including the US, UK, and much of Europe.\n\nPlease provide the details of your other passport or travel document, and I'll be happy to assist you further!",
